 ''Bomber Harris''. Doubleday. {{ISBN|978-0-385-11258-1}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Ungv\u00e1ry |first1=Kriszti\u00e1n |authorlink1=Kriszti\u00e1n Ungv\u00e1ry |title=A magyar honv\u00e9ds\u00e9g a m\u00e1sodik vil\u00e1gh\u00e1bor\u00faban | trans-title=The Hungarian Defense Forces in the Second World War | date=2004 |publisher=Osiris |location=Budapest |isbn=9633896851 |language=Hungarian |ref=harv}}\n* United States Strategic Bombing Survey. [http://www.anesi.com/ussbs01.htm ''Summary Report (Pacific War)''] 1 July 1946.\n* United States Strategic Bombing Survey. [http://www.anesi.com/ussbs02.htm ''Summary Report (European War)''] 30 September 1945.\n* United States Strategic Bombing Survey. [http://www.allworldwars.com/The%20Defeat%20of%20the%20German%20Air%20Force.html ''The Defeat of the German Air Force.''] 1947.\n* United States Strategic Bombing Survey. ''The Effects of Strategic Bombing on German Transportation''. 1947.\n* United States Strategic Bombing Survey. ''The Effects of Strategic Bombing on the German War Economy''. 1945.\n* Willmott, H.P. (1991). ''The Great Crusade.'' Free Press, 1991. {{ISBN|978-0-02-934716-4}}\n* Wood & Dempster (1990) ''The Narrow Margin'' Chapter \"Second Phase\" {{ISBN|978-0-87474-929-8}}\n* Wood, Derek and Dempster, Derek. (1990). ''The Narrow Margin: The Battle of Britain and the Rise of Air Power'', London: Tri-Service Press, third revised edition. {{ISBN|1-85488-027-6}}.\n* Young, Kevin. [http://www.counterpunch.org/young08092008.html \"The Path to Hiroshima and Nagasaki \u2013 Targeting Civilians\"], CounterPunch, 9\u201310 August 2008.\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{Cite journal|last=Childers |first=Thomas  |title=Facilis descensus averni est: The Allied Bombing of Germany and the Issue of German Suffering |doi=10.1163/1569161053623624 |issn=1569-1616 |year=2008 |journal=Central European History |volume=38 |page=75}}\n* Clodfelter, Mark. \"Aiming to Break Will: America's World War II Bombing of Ger