hara]]. It is licensed in North America by [[CPM Manga]], in [[Poland]] by [[Japonica Polonica Fantastica|JPF]]<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://manga.tanuki.pl/strony/manga/53-legend-of-lemnear/rec/26 |title=Legend of Lemnear |author=\u0141ukasz Lipi\u0144ski |date=30 September 2007 |journal=Tanuki.pl |volume=843 |publisher=Ma\u0142gorzata Kaczarowska |accessdate=27 June 2011 |issn=1898-8296 |language=Polish |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110621075648/http://manga.tanuki.pl/strony/manga/53-legend-of-lemnear/rec/26 |archive-date=21 June 2011 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> and in Russia by [[Comics Factory]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://comics-factory.ru/?page_id=5|title=Comic books index|publisher=[[Comics Factory]]|language=Russian|accessdate=5 September 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111020144308/http://comics-factory.ru/?page_id=5|archive-date=20 October 2011|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It focuses heavily on the \"swords and sorcery\" genre, and in typical Urushihara style provides a great deal of [[fan service]].\n\nThe story focuses around the title character, Lemnear, who according to prophecy is the Champion of Silver. She seeks revenge on the evil wizard Gardein and the master he serves, attempting to avenge the slaughter of her people.\n\n==Plot summary==\nLemnear, a young warrior girl, arrives to a city ruled by the corrupt warlord Vuan. She seeks revenge on the evil wizard Gardin, Vuan's master, who slaughtered Lemnear's people back when she was a child in the search of a mysterious, prophesized Champion of Silver. Eventually, Lemnear confronts Gardin, but she is knocked out with a magic blast and sent to the city's dungeons, where young girls are retained in order to join Vuan's [[harem]]. There Lemnear finds about the prophecy from an old mage, who tells her the Champion of Silver will turn a Champion of Bronze into Gold and will destroy the evil Barol, the ultimate mastermind behind Gardin and Vuan. In order to rescue a friend from the dungeons, Lemnear infiltrates the harem, but Vuan brainwashes her into becoming another slave. It's thanks to the magic choker that she breaks out and manages to kill Vuan, not without hearding from Gardin that Barol challenges her from his Castle of Valquisas. Upon reaching the castle, she learns of another survivor of her people, Mesh, whom Gardin had believed to be the Champion of Silver and is actually the Champion of Bronze. She fights and kills Gardin, but he turns out to be just the enchanted right arm of Barol. The villain reveals to be a Champion of Gold himself who was raised up by dark powers after his village kicked him out for being a human hybrid. Lemnear and Mesh fight him, defeating both his human and dragon form, but he then turns into a stone giant and moves on to conquer the world. Realizing the prophecy, Lemnear awakes her power through her choker, turns Mesh into a Champion of Gold and they both together destroy Barol's weak spot, killing him for good.\n\n==Cast==\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Japanese===\n*[[Eiko Yamada]] - Lemnear\n*[[Keiko Yokozawa]] - Lian\n*[[Ryusei Nakao]] - Mesh\n*[[Akio Ohtsuka]] - Vuan \n*[[Iemasa Kayumi]] - Gardin\n*Nobuo Tanaka - Barol\n*[[Ry\u016bji Saikachi]] - Sendoshi/Old Mage\n{{col-break|gap=2em}}\n===English===\n*[[Jezabel Montero]] - Lemnear\n*[[Veronica Taylor]] - Lian\n*[[Greg Baglia]] - Mesh\n*[[Bill Rogers (voice actor)|Bill Rogers]] - Vuan \n*[[Bart Shattuck]] - Gardin\n*[[Bill Rogers (voice actor)|Bill Rogers]] - Old Mage\n*[[Harvey Shane]] - Barol\n*[[Wendy Scharfman]] - Mother\n{{col-end}}\n==Reception==\nSimilarities between Lemnear and the Taarakian Taarna from ''[[Heavy Metal (film)|Heavy Metal]]'', including her sword, hair color, and mode of transportation, were noted by critics.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.themanime.org/viewreview.php?id=1288 |title=THEM Anime Reviws 4.0 - Legend of Lemnear |access-date=2019-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331132452/http://www.themanime.org/viewreview.php?id=1288 |archive-date=2019-03-31 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ann|anime|690|1989 anime}}\n*{{ann|manga|2821|1991 manga}}\n\n{{Anime International Company}}\n\n[[Category:1987 anime OVAs]]\n[[Category:1991 manga]]\n[[Category:Anime International Company]]\n[[Category:Central Park Media]]\n[[Category:Fantasy anime and manga]]\n[[Category:Sh\u014dnen manga]]\n\n{{anime-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Black Walnut", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot summary:syntax: \u00a8finds about\u00a8 -> \u00a8learns of\u00a8", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legend_of_Lemnear"}
